  "title": "QUALITY ASSURANCE ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>We are looking for a <strong>Quality Assurance Engineer</strong> to ensure that all products and processes meet customer, regulatory, and internal quality requirements. The role involves inspection, documentation, root cause analysis, and continuous improvement activities within a mechanical\nmanufacturing environment.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Implement and maintain quality control procedures in accordance with company and\ncustomer requirements</li><li>Conduct incoming, in-process, and final inspections of mechanical parts and assemblies</li><li>Review and approve inspection reports, route cards, and quality records</li><li>Handle non-conformance (NCR), corrective and preventive actions (CAPA)</li><li>Perform root cause analysis and support improvement initiatives</li><li>Support customer audits, internal audits, and supplier audits</li><li>Liaise with production, engineering, and suppliers on quality issues</li><li>Ensure compliance with ISO / customer quality standards and drawings</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Mechanical Engineering</strong> or related field</li><li>Minimum <strong>3 years of experience</strong> in Quality Assurance within a manufacturing environment</li><li>Knowledge of mechanical drawings, GD&T, and inspection tools (e.g. vernier, micrometer, CMM is an advantage)</li><li>Familiar with quality systems such as <strong>ISO 9001 / AS9100</strong> (advantage)</li><li>Strong problem-solving and communication skills</li><li>Able to work independently and as part of a team</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Skills (Advantage)</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in aerospace / precision engineering environment</li><li>Knowledge of NDT, FAI, PPAP, or customer-specific requirements </li><li>Audit experience (internal or external)</li></ul><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure product and process quality meet customer and company requirements</li><li>Perform incoming, in-process, and final inspection of mechanical parts</li><li>Handle non-conformance reports (NCR), corrective and preventive actions (CAPA)</li><li>Review inspection reports, drawings, and quality documents</li><li>Support internal, customer, and supplier audits</li><li>Work closely with production and engineering teams on quality issues</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Mechanical Engineering or related field</li><li>Minimum 3 years of QA experience in a manufacturing environment</li><li>Able to read mechanical drawings and use basic inspection tools</li><li>Familiar with ISO 9001 / AS9100 quality systems (advantage)</li><li>Good communication and problem-solving skills</li></ul><p></p>",
